x multiplication. This improves upon both state-of-the-art\ncomplexity bounds $O\\tilde{~}(tD^2)$ and $O\\tilde{~}(D^\\omega)$, since $\\omega\n< 3$ and $t\\le D$. Practical experiments, based on the libraries msolve and\nPML, confirm the high practical benefit.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 18 Feb 2022 14:49:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 15 May 2022 22:12:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-17"}
